s are an interdisciplinary, transnational group of scholars from gender studies, feminist theory, history, anthropology, sociology, women’s studies, and literature. Among the issues they address are: the impact of migration, education, early socialization of gender roles, the role of the media in perpetuating and shaping negative stereotypes, the gendered nature of language, women and the media, literature by women, and local appropriation of gender and feminist theory. Each author offers a fresh and unique perspective on the current process of survival strategies and postcommunist identity reconstruction among Ukrainian women in their current climate of patriarchalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aFeminismzUkraine. 0aWomenzUkrainexSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aWomenzUkraine. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aBilaniuk, Laada, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaydenko, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHrycak, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKis’, Oksana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Sarah D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRewakowicz, Maria G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubchak, Marian J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSolari, Cinzia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaran, Liudmyla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTytarenko, Mariia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZhurzhenko, Tatiana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gru